                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13101519" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 9 Sep 2011 19:57:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to drop buffer size to 64k, as is the RandomAccessReader default.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13101524" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 9 Sep 2011 20:03:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there anywhere we actually need non-default buffer sizes?  I think we should probably rip out that constructor parameter (on both RAR and SW) to force everyone to be sane whether they like it or not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See also: the 10MB buffer in streaming and the 8MB one in IndexWriter.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13101559" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 9 Sep 2011 20:59:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;v2 removes unnecessary bufferSize parameters across the call heirarchy.  Main exception is CRAR, to which I added&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// TODO refactor &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; to separate concept of &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;buffer to avoid lots of read() syscalls&quot;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;compression buffer&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13101570" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 9 Sep 2011 21:14:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13101576" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 9 Sep 2011 21:20:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
